    "description": "Manipal Digital Health Holdings Services invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Full Stack Developer at our Madurai location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout Manipal Digital Health Holdings Services:\nManipal Digital Health Holdings Services is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Optimize application performance and ensure high availability\n• Participate in on-call rotation for production support\n• Collaborate with cross-functional teams including product, design, and QA\n• Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code\n• Deploy and manage applications on cloud platforms like AWS, Azure, or GCP\n• Integrate third-party APIs and services\n• Implement new features based on product requirements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Microservices\n• Proficiency in JavaScript\n• Proficiency in Machine Learning\n• Proficiency in Kubernetes\n• Proficiency in CI/CD\n• Proficiency in MongoDB\n• Proficiency in Python\n• Proficiency in AWS\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Madurai, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Manipal Digital Health Holdings Services!",
